<tmc-service-inc>
<pub id="RM0251U">
<servcat id="35">
<name>SUSPENSION &amp; AXLE</name>
<section id="1000J_S000X" variety="S000X">
<name>TIRE AND WHEEL</name>
<ttl id="1000J_S000X_738JZ_T00GU" variety="T00GU">
<name>TIRE PRESSURE WARNING SYSTEM</name>
<para id="RM000000XN5008X" category="J" type-id="3037E" name-id="TW0JF-01" from="200601">
<dtccode/>
<dtcname>TC and CG Terminal Circuit</dtcname>
<subpara id="RM000000XN5008X_02" type-id="60" category="03" proc-id="RM0250U___00005JA00001">
<name>DESCRIPTION</name>
<content5 releasenbr="1">
<ptxt>DTC output mode is set by connecting terminals 13 (TC) and 4 (CG) of the DLC3. The DTCs are indicated by the blinking of the tire pressure warning light.</ptxt>
</content5>
</subpara>
<subpara id="RM000000XN5008X_03" type-id="32" category="03" proc-id="RM0250U___00005JB00001">
<name>WIRING DIAGRAM</name>
<content5 releasenbr="1">
<figure>
<graphic graphicname="E110507E13" width="7.106578999in" height="4.7836529in"/>
</figure>
<atten4>
<ptxt>When each warning light blinks continuously, a ground short in the wiring of terminal TC of the DLC3 or an internal ground short in an ECU connected to this circuit may have occurred.</ptxt>
</atten4>
</content5>
</subpara>
<subpara id="RM000000XN5008X_04" type-id="51" category="05" proc-id="RM0250U___00005XC00001">
<name>INSPECTION PROCEDURE</name>
<content5 releasenbr="1">
<atten3>
<ptxt>It is necessary to register an ID code after replacing the tire pressure warning valve and transmitter and/or the tire pressure warning ECU (See page <xref label="Seep01" href="RM000000XN1008X"/>).</ptxt>
</atten3>
</content5>
</subpara>
<subpara id="RM000000XN5008X_05" type-id="01" category="01">
<name>PROCEDURE</name>
<testgrp id="RM000000XN5008X_05_0013" proc-id="RM0250U___00005XD00001">
<testtitle>CHECK HARNESS AND CONNECTOR (DLC3 - TIRE PRESSURE WARNING ECU)</testtitle>
<content6 releasenbr="1">
<test1>
<ptxt>Disconnect the E60 ECU connector.</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname="E129465E01" width="2.775699831in" height="3.779676365in"/>
</figure>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>Measure the resistance according to the value(s) in the table below.</ptxt>
<spec>
<title>Standard resistance</title>
<table>
<tgroup cols="2" align="center">
<colspec colname="COL1" colwidth="2.07in"/>
<colspec colname="COL2" colwidth="2.06in"/>
<thead>
<row>
<entry valign="middle">
<ptxt>Tester Connection</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry valign="middle">
<ptxt>Specified Condition</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
</thead>
<tbody>
<row>
<entry valign="middle">
<ptxt>E60-3 (TC) - E10-13 (TC)</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry morerows="1" valign="middle">
<ptxt>Below 1 Ω</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
<row>
<entry valign="middle">
<ptxt>E10-4 (CG) - Body ground</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
</tbody>
</tgroup>
</table>
</spec>
</test1>
</content6>
<res>
<down ref="RM000000XN5008X_05_0014" fin="true">OK</down>
<right ref="RM000000XN5008X_05_0015" fin="true">NG</right>
</res>
</testgrp>
<testgrp id="RM000000XN5008X_05_0014">
<testtitle>PROCEED TO NEXT CIRCUIT INSPECTION SHOWN IN PROBLEM SYMPTOMS TABLE</testtitle>
</testgrp>
<testgrp id="RM000000XN5008X_05_0015">
<testtitle>REPAIR OR REPLACE HARNESS OR CONNECTOR</testtitle>
</testgrp>
</subpara>
</para>
</ttl>
</section>
</servcat>
</pub>
